The paper discusses Fog networking, which is a new architecture for computation, storage, communication, and network management that brings the Cloud closer to the end users. This topic falls under the category of Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the allocation of functionalities and engineering artifacts that may use a Fog architecture, which could fall under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
